column16: Dispense interval standard deviation: the standard deviation of the patient's dispense intervals.  As the dispense interval average approaches the supply, the SD value must be exceedingly small if the protocol is being followed.  The standard deviation is a way to judge whether a dispense interval average that is less than the supply actually reflects provision according to protocol.
